{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nThe epic 88ab feature-branch flow (S3) replicates refs/heads/feature/* to the GitHub mirror so g2p's workflow_dispatch(ref=refs/heads/feature/<name>) resolves. Side effect: test.yml, eval.yml, optionality.yml all trigger on push: branches: ['**'], so every replicated feature/* branch-head push fans out 3 extra CI runs on the mirror. These runs cast NO Verified vote (gerrit-verify workflow_dispatch is the sole Verified source), so they are pure cost/noise, not part of the gate.\n\n## What\n- Scope feature/** OUT of the push triggers of test.yml, eval.yml, optionality.yml (e.g. push: branches-ignore: ['feature/**'], preserving main + pull_request), so replicated feature branches do not trigger redundant mirror CI.\n- Verify the gerrit-verify (Verified) path is unaffected.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] test/eval/optionality no longer run on pushes to refs/heads/feature/* on the mirror\n- [ ] main + PR triggers unchanged; gerrit-verify Verified path unaffected\n- [ ] A feature/* branch push produces zero push-triggered mirror runs (evidence)"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783063077258610001,"uuid":"dea3995c-d0b3-4982-a297-947d020c8472"}